        By
        <span><a href="/person/d/nicole-darrah">Nicole Darrah</a><!----><span class="article-source"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.foxnews.com/"> | Fox News</a></span></span></span><!----></div><div class="article-social"><div class="social-icons"><ul><li class="fb"><a href="#" rel="nofollow">Facebook</a></li><li class="tw"><a href="#" rel="nofollow">Twitter</a></li><li class="flipboard"><a rel="nofollow">Flipboard</a></li><li class="comments"><a href="#" rel="nofollow"><span>Comments</span></a></li><li class="print"><a href="/us/south-carolina-boy-befriends-officer-at-chick-fil-a.print" rel="nofollow">Print</a></li><li class="email"><a href="#" rel="nofollow">Email</a></li></ul></div></div></div></header><div class="article-content-wrap sticky-columns"><div class="article-content"><div class="article-body"><div source="" class="image-ct featured featured-image"><div class="m"><picture><source media="(max-width: 767px)" srcset="https://a57.foxnews.com/static.foxnews.com/foxnews.com/content/uploads/2019/01/1470/828/police-and-kid.jpg?ve=1&amp;tl=1 2x"><source media="(min-width: 767px)" srcset="https://a57.foxnews.com/static.foxnews.com/foxnews.com/content/uploads/2019/01/1862/1048/police-and-kid.jpg?ve=1&amp;tl=1 2x"><img src="https://a57.foxnews.com/a57.foxnews.com/static.foxnews.com/foxnews.com/content/uploads/2019/01/640/320/1862/1048/police-and-kid.jpg?ve=1&amp;tl=1?ve=1&amp;tl=1" alt="Greenville Police Officer Terence Brister said the young boy who befriended him in a South Carolina Chick-fil-A on Friday is &quot;the very reason&quot; he's served his community and the U.S."></picture></div><div class="info"><div class="caption"><p>
          Greenville Police Officer Terence Brister said the young boy who befriended him in a South Carolina Chick-fil-A on Friday is &quot;the very reason&quot; he's served his community and the U.S.
          <span>(Terence Brister)</span></p></div></div></div><p class="speakable">A <a href="https://www.foxnews.com/us/south-carolina-inmates-to-get-tablets-for-phone-calls-watching-movies">South Carolina</a> police officer made a new friend last week when a young boy thanked him for his service at a local <a href="https://www.foxnews.com/food-drink/chick-fil-a-will-soon-be-the-no-3-fast-food-chain-in-america-research-firm-claims">Chick-fil-A</a>.</p><div class="ad-container tablet"><div data-ad-pos="tablet" data-ad-size="300x250" data-ad-lz="" class="ad gpt ad-h-250"></div><!----></div><div class="ad-container mobile"><div data-ad-pos="mobile" data-ad-size="300x250" data-ad-lz="" class="ad gpt ad-h-250"></div><!----></div><p class="speakable">Terence Brister, an officer with the Greenville Police Department who says he served in the&#xA0;<a href="https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/military/marines">Marine Corps</a>, wrote on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/terence.brister/posts/10210629266282568">Facebook</a>&#xA0;that the boy approached him at the&#xA0;restaurant on Friday to thank him.</p><div data-ad-pos="inread" data-ad-size="1x1" class="ad gpt ad-h-1"></div><p><a href="https://www.foxnews.com/us/north-carolina-kids-heartwarming-note-deputy-dad-patrol-car"><strong>NORTH CAROLINA KIDS LEAVE HEARTWARMING NOTE ON DEPUTY DAD&apos;S PATROL CAR</strong></a></p><p>To thank him, in turn, for such a <a href="https://www.foxnews.com/lifestyle/walmart-customers-kind-gesture-for-veteran-goes-viral-im-grateful-for-you">kind gesture</a>, Brister said he &quot;took [the boy] to the counter and bought him a cookie.&quot;</p><p>But the boy took the kindness a step further, and gave the officer a gift card to Chick-fil-A.</p><div class="ad-container mobile"><div data-ad-pos="mobile" data-ad-size="300x251" data-ad-lz="" class="ad gpt ad-h-250"></div><!----></div><p><a href="https://www.foxnews.com/apps-products"><strong>CLICK HERE TO GET THE FOX NEWS APP</strong></a></p><p>&quot;He is the very reason I have served in USMC, State Police and now City Police. The faith, innocence and love of a child is immeasurable,&quot; Brister wrote. &quot;In a world that&#x2019;s divided by racial tension, prejudice and discrimination, why can&#x2019;t adults be more like kids. He didn&#x2019;t see black or white, he saw only a law enforcement officer and who he called a hero.&quot;</p><p>Brister thanked the boy&apos;s parents &quot;for raising a child who loves everyone,&quot; and said that despite some people&apos;s negative feelings toward law enforcement, &quot;it&apos;s days like today that God often reminds me of those who love, honor and respect the badge and uniform.&quot;</p><!----></div><div class="article-meta"><div class="author-bio">Nicole Darrah covers breaking and trending news for FoxNews.com. Follow her on Twitter <a href="https://twitter.com/nicoledarrah" target="_blank">@nicoledarrah</a>.</div></div><footer class="article-footer"><!----><!----><div data-uid="ar-2" class="vendor-unit tablet-desktop"></div><div data-uid="ar-3" class="vendor-unit tablet-desktop"></div><div data-uid="ar-1" class="vendor-unit mobile"></div><div class="vendor-unit vendor-yieldmo"><div class="ad-container mobile-tablet yieldmo"><div id="cu_article_4" class="ad cu"></div></div></div><div class="vendor-unit vendor-yieldmo"><div id="cu_article_3" class="ad-container yieldmo"></div></div><div data-uid="ar-8" class="vendor-unit tablet-desktop"></div><div id="commenting" class="article-comments"></div></footer></div><aside class="sidebar sidebar-article sidebar-primary desktop"><div class="sticky-region"><div class="sidebar-columns"><div class="ad-container desktop"><div data-ad-pos="desktop" data-ad-size="300x250,300x600" data-ad-lz="" class="ad gpt "></div><span class="advert-txt"></span></div><div class="embed-media advanced"><div class="ad-container htu-container"><div class="ad gpt" id="htu-unit" data-type="htu" data-ad-size="1x2"></div></div></div><div dat